second time we visited and it did not disappoint located at the end of le_duan opposite the sofitel this neat little cafe offers a nice spacious interior and comfortable seating free wifi friendly staff and of course great drinks this cafe is a bit quieter than the other coffee houses which is good for a more intimate gathering we ordered an ice chocolate without cream and a blueberry smoothie and a green tea tirimisu to munch on the ice chocolate was a winner very chocolate like without the super sugary taste it was an original iced chocolate at its best the blueberry smoothie was very nice not too milky or heavy and served very chilled the green tea tirimisu cake was a bit misleading as the green tea flavour was very pronounced but the tirimisu component was missing it was a nice cake but not what it was said to be all in all fantastic outing at this nice cafe

i couldnt wait to go to a pet cafe this one was a little far from where we live but it was totally worth our drive the place is very clean for having many animals and their coffee is actually one of the best we have wasnt too strong or watery they have quite a few differnt birds you can hold on the first floor along with a few dogs on the second floor they have cat and a bunnies scattered throughout there are hampsters and frogs in cages i would definitly recomend this place if you like pets and dont have any allergies

the bountiful set menus are a definite plus with amazing taste i really enjoy the fusion tastes of korean and american french mix the service was excellent because in the set we switched out a pasta that my friends tried already and it was no problem with the rest of the set menu in tact there are also korean food in the menu but the pasta is a must try also tried their calaone my first time plenty of chicken and cheese yum the place is cute in terms of decor looks like a cafe too but definitely a quality for dining in with friends or couples service may be slow on a busy day but refeshments are delightful with bread and honey if you are in the area its definitely worth a try

i ordered a cheesecake just because i missed having some authentic ones after having failed attempts in other cafes in china and vietnam i liked to seek out the foreign made cafes such as this one with a french taste it was nice and quiet in the cafe with good music and modern decorations the layout was wide and free there were french guests a family beside my table where the manager who is also french kept in conversation with them i was impressed by the manager s presence because he would overlook everything to be quality the waitresses also spoke english which was helpful there were many choices of desserts that looked good but i had already eaten lunch i chose my favorite the_cheesecake yes it may be pricey but when a girl has her cravings a girls gotta eat

ng cu lâ n la mô t điê m tham_quan hoa n toa n mơ i toanh n đô du li ch đa la t chi mơ i va o hoa t đô ng mô t thâ t la mô t điê m du li ch nă m dươ i lu ng sâu ti nh châ t hoang da la ng ma n va đu ng ha ng to a la c đi a giơ i thôn suô i ca n la t h la c dương lâm_đô ng thung lu ng rô ng ha na y co mô t suô i y quanh la nguô n nươ c mô t la ng ngươ i cơ_ho sinh sô ng co go i la dankya bao bo c lâ n ng thu hiê n la nh thâ y ngươ i chi che mă t la i bă ng hai chi trươ c lâ n bi bă t gâ n hê t ca i cu lâ n cu ng co thê bơ i thung lu ng na y cu ng co râ t nhiê u cu lâ n vi ma u thân ma u da cu lâ n mo c nhiê u dươ i ta n rư ng thông va mô i bi y no chuyê n thân tư ma u va ng da bo ma u đen tro chi câ n mưa xuô ng chu ng la i pha t triê n trơ la i la ng cu lâ n xe chu ng cư lươ n đươ ng hai la thông xanh la ng nươ c cu a suô i va ng kê cư thê tơ i thâ y la ng cu lâ n ca m gia c đâ u tiên la co gi vi chi thâ y mô t chiê c ng sơ sa i mô t i đâ t trô ng vơ i nhiê u loa i xe đâ u giô ng mô t i giư xe mô t ga i giư ng kiêm soa t ve kiêm giư xe n ve đô ng ngươ i biê t giư xe miê n phi o đi đươ ng co chiê c xe ngư a vâ y la nhă m hươ ng mô t chiê c xe ngư a gô đê bươ c xuô ng ha ng trăm bâ c thang tâ m mă t â y mơ i ca m nhâ n vê ca i ky vy cu a la ng cu lâ n nê u ca c khu du li ch kha c đa la t tâ n du ng ng tha m hoa la m không_gian la ng ma n thi ng ngươ i la m du li ch ta o kha ch mô t sư thi ch thu đươ c vươ t va chinh_phu c sư gian kho ca m nhâ n sư hoang_sơ cu a nu i rư ng ngoa i viê c nê u thi ch kha ch bo nga n đô ng thuê mô t chiê c xe jeep đê cu ng lao xuô ng chô m đoa n đươ ng km quanh khu vư c kha ch se sư du ng đôi chân đê xuô ng lu ng va đô i loa i chu đa o chen co da i chen ca ca c cu lâ n la hoa kim_châm vơ i ma u va ng nha t hê t ca c bâ c thang la hai câ u treo mô i câ u đươ c o vê bơ i sơ i ca p lơ n cư c ky an toa n câ u nhu n chân mô t ca i la câ u đong_đưa ca i đong_đưa â y co mu i co da i thoang thoa ng co tiê ng cu a gio lu a rư ng la m xôn_xao lo ng dô c trơ i xuô ng cuô i dô c ca ngươ i ma t rươ i phi a đâ u la ng ta n thông thă ng vu t dươ i la t nga n hoa va la la ng cu lâ n â n hiê n sương kho i cu a thung lu ng cư thê thi ch thi cư đi muô n dư ng chân thi co ghê gô co xi ch đu gô kha ch ngô i ma ng tâ m mă t nhi n rư ng thông nhi n hô nươ c to mo thư cu lâ n la gi đi tư na y đê n kha c la i leo câ u treo gă n ng đe n măng_sông va tơ i chơ chô m hô m la ng đuô c nă m hô co sân_chơi đê kha ch la i đêm tâ t nhiên la thă p đuô c huyê n a o ng nha da nh kha ch đêm kiê n tru c tây_nguyên thi ch rư ng đêm ke m mo i di ch vu uô ng cư tiê p tu c đi đươ ng c ng suô i ca n hai la cu lâ n nê u thi ch thi thuê chiê c be tư che o hô câu ca hoă c mô t chiê c câ u gô nho dô c trơ i đi nh đô i ma ngă m ca mô t thung lu ng mênh_mông mô t i co rô ng la da tra i đô t lư a tra i đêm thi ch hơ p vơ i ca c n tre co mô t ma ng nươ c gâ n đi nh câ u mưa ma vâ t du ng đê hư ng nươ c la mô t nô i đô ng rô i la i leo xe ngư a da o hoă c va o chơ chô m hô m đê coi buôn n ca i gi mô t di ch vu cu ng đô c đa o ta i la tă m tiên tâ t nhiên la tă m dươ i suô i ca n giư a lau la ch pha i hiê u la vâ n mă c đô che ng chô ki n đa o chư pha i kho a thân hoa it all started years ago with a stroll around town to some sight seeing i stumbled into this place after noticing the crowds on my morning walks it s been a wrap eversince places that only have a few options on the menu are a plus because that means the food is always fresh here you can either choose to have or bun_bo_hue as your meal the_pho was very good i ordered the bun_bo_hue to go for lunch later that day fast forward to now and the quality has still remained spectacular the owner always has a smile on his face and you can tell he appreciates his customers which is rare for a place that stays this busy the food here makes me happy and letting everbody know is the purpose for the review
